  "prompt": "How can I get past my fear of being hurt in relationships?",
  "response": "Here are some strategies that might help:\n\n1. Therapy\n- Work with a professional to process past traumas\n- Learn healthy relationship skills\n- Build self-confidence and emotional resilience\n\n2. Self-reflection\n- Understand the root of your fears\n- Recognize past relationship patterns\n- Practice self-awareness\n\n3. Gradual vulnerability\n- Start with small emotional risks\n- Build trust slowly\n- Communicate your feelings and boundaries\n\n4. Positive self-talk\n- Challenge negative thoughts\n- Affirm your own worth\n- Remind yourself that not all relationships will be painful\n\n5. Healing past wounds\n- Process previous relationship traumas\n- Practice self-compassion\n- Learn from past experiences without letting them define you\n\n6. Develop healthy relationship skills\n- Learn effective communication\n- Set clear boundaries\n- Recognize healthy vs. unhealthy relationship dynamics\n\n7. Build self-esteem\n- Focus on personal growth\n- Develop independent interests\n- Value yourself outside of relationships\n\n8. Be open to risk\n- Understand that vulnerability is necessary for genuine connection\n- Accept that some emotional risk is part of meaningful relationships\n\nRemember that healing takes time and patience. Consider professional counseling for personalized support.\n\nWould you like to discuss any of these strategies in more depth?",
